                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2" color="#FFF8DC"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> He was tired...<br />It was more than 2 moons away when he rode outside the Keep in search of his quest.He had missed all his friends, the warmth of the fireplace, clean sheets, a bed.But most of all it was her smile he longed to see most.And her eyes...<br />He lowered his head towards the head of his faithfull great war horse.<br /><br />"I know you are tired also Noracor.You are not forced to follow my request.But i think we are very close. Very close to home.If we keep forward we can reach it before sundown..."<br /><br />Noracor fastened his pace as even as if he could sence his masters wish before he could even spell it to him...<br />Indeed they were close.Soon they saw the battlements of the rose-like Keep.<br />Man and horse charged in the middle of the road as if some fiendish creature was hunting them.<br /><br />"Cavalier approaching"... shouted the guard above the main Gate.<br /><br />"Which banners does he ride under?" yelled the captain of the guard from below.<br /><br />"Mithaniel Marr's milord... and i think i can see our banner also on his shield" replied the guard.<br /><br />"Raise the portculis!" shouted the captain, "someone lead his horse to the stables and take care of it"...<br /><br />So he crossed the bridge again, his heart beating faster that before.<br />As he dismounted, he wispered some thankfull words to Noracor ears and let the reigns to a men-at-arms.<br /><br />"Hail to thee, Agrivar" he said to the captain<br /><br />"Greetings Griffonheart. How art thee?" <br /><br />"Tired... but i return with Mithaniels blessings. I found what i was seeking"<br /><br />"Very good.I do understand that you are tired but the Lord wishes to speak with you.He ordered us to sent you to him as soon as you were back"<br /><br />"Anounce to him my return.I will be at his office as soon as i change my armor and wear something more formal"<br /><br />....<br /><br />Closing the door behind him, he steped into his room.A pleasant smell reached his nostrils.There, on his bed beside his pellow, was a handfull of white roses.Under them was a purple silken cord.Gently he raised one rose and smelled it while he was looking at the cord.It looked familiar.<br /><br />"Yes... she rides under those colors... Purple colors.." he said to himself.<br />Laying down the rose and the cord, he started removing his plate mail.<br />Reaching in a wooden chest, he pulled off a new suit of chain mail armor and a white winter cloak.As he was dressing up he took the cord and placed it under the chain mail at the place of his heart.<br />Blowing the torch off and taking his sword , he left the room without looking back.<br />...without looking back at the now dark room<br />...at the rose<br />...at the flower that was now slightly different... it had turned black.<br /><br />...<br /><br />He stood in front of the closed door of the Lords office. Following the knights Code and Meassure he knocked thrice but he did not enter.<br /><br />"Come inside" said a soft melodic voice.<br /><br />Gently he pushed the wooden door and entered the room.Closing the door behind him he took 4 steps into the room and bowed deeply.<br /><br />"You summoned me , milord" <br /><br />" yes yes... i wish to speak with you Griffonheart"<br /><br />He could never sence the temper of his Lord.Elves where known for their great wisdom and that they have been granted with  immortality.So their faces never showed up any feelings.<br /><br />"What is it about great Lord?"<br /><br />"As you know , you were away for many days and nights knight.During your absence many things have taken place.I will not bother you with all of them but there is one that i wish to speak to you for.I believe you do know a young squire by the name Lorein"<br /><br />...echoes of battle... horses charging... men screaming in pain...suddenly a heavy lance piereced his heart... lorein... Lorein...<br /><br />"Yes my Lord , i do know the squire you speak off.I have vowed to Mithaniel Marr to be her protector and champion after she saved my life."<br /><br />"Well there is a slightly problem with that matter, Knight. Squire Lorein has been casted away from our orders under the charges of breaking the Code and the Meassure.She was allowed to take her personal items and she left our Keep 1 week ago.She will no longer be under our protection and the next time one of us should encounter her, he should treat her as a stranger."<br /><br />...he reposted to the ogres attack... but as he was ready to strike the deadly blow a greatsword severed both of his legs at knee-hight...<br /><br />"But Lord, which part of the Code did she violated?" he asked ... his voice cracked...<br /><br />"She was seen speaking to a man not worthy of our attencion.A man under our status.A man that is considered our enemy."<br /><br />"But milord... who is that man? i know that Lorein treats our enemies as enemies, i have seen what see can do in battle.So she would never come in friendly terms with one of those..."<br /><br />"You are not to judge my decisions knight.You are to accept them.You have been noticed about her leaving and from now on i expect you to treat her accordingly. You are dismissed."<br /><br />He bowed again and he left the room speachless.<br /><br />....<br /><br />The guard stood watch in the highest post of the battlements.Freezing winds made him cover his shoulders better under his heavy cloak.Suddenly he heard armored steps behind him.<br /><br />"Who goes there? Come closer so i can identify you but keep your hands away from your weapons"<br /><br />"You are relieved of your post soldier.Go to your barracks and rest" said a deep voice under a plate helm.It seemed as if the mans voice came from the deeper layers of hell.<br /><br />"But milord Griffonheart arent you tired? You had a long journey. It is you that you must be resting now." replied the soldier although the thought of a bed and a fireplace made his heart tumbling.<br /><br />"This is an order soldier and you are not to question it.Now go " ...<br /><br />The man-at-arms left his post as quickly as possible.<br /><br />....<br /><br /><br />There he was now.<br />Standing on the battlements.<br />He wasnt cold.<br />That cord under his breastplate seemed to be heating him and keeping him warm.<br />He was all he ever  dreamed to be.<br />A solemn warrior, evils bane, goods champion, helper of the weaks , defender of the poor, first to charge and face the enemy.He had chosen a difficult road to walk.But he have endured all the dangers.Because he was doing what his heart told him to do.He was following Mithaniel Marrs will.He had witnessed discraced knights and their downfall.He even knew that discraced knights still existed in the order he served, masking their actions under the Code and the Meassure.<br />And there he was now standing alone on a place that once seemed friendly... when she was around...<br />But she was gone...<br />...gone because of an order...<br />...gone because she followed what the Code and the Meassure ment for her , and not because of what it meant for the others...<br /><br />He looked at the starlit sky...<br /><br />"Forgive me Great Paladin... because for my first time i do not know what to do.All these years i have served you well.Because even if what i had to do was difficult, the path was lighted by your presence and guideance.But now i stand on a crossroad.For the first time in my life.I do not know what to choose... please forgive me..."<br /><br />....<br /><br />hours passed, he stood there motionless.<br />But a great battle was fought into his body.His heart was dueling his mind.<br /><br />He had to choose...<br />before the sunrise...<br /><br /> <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /></span id="msg"></font></td>
                    </tr>
