                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2" color="#FFF8DC"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> The wings were blowing like they were trying to rip off all the trees from their roots. The small house was under the siege of the weavy rain but it withstanded it just fine...<br /><br />Inside a small bearder figure moved through the shadows throwing another log into the fireplace...<br /><br />"Damn that weather... I should have never left my home in Thurgandin"...<br /><br />Blowing his nose noisily he threw his aged body on a comfortable armchair.<br /><br />"Well, if i am not allowed to sleep maybe i can spend my time doing something else." said the old dwarf reaching for a carving knife and a piece of wood.<br />Though those were not the tools of his profession he loved wood-carving. When he was not at the company of his forge and his hammer , he carved finely figures on wood. All the furnishing and the sculpture inside his small house witnessed it.<br /><br />Watching the flames consuming the log in the fireplace his hands run over the small piece of wood with love, just before he started carving it...<br /><br />-----------------<br /><br />Say will you dream of me tonight under moonless skies.... a final dream within the shadows...<br /><br />--------------<br /><br />He was staring the flames dancing over the almost comsumed for too long now, when the old dwarfs eyes widened in surprise...<br /><br />The dancing flames have formed the figure of a handsome man clad in plate mail armor.Only his head was uncovered.Blonde hair run over his shoulders, like a waterfall...<br />The burning figure noded at him<br /><br />"Greetings Boldaim... I see that time has treated you well olf dwarf.Please listen to me because i will only say this once. Three moons from now you will be visited by a man who has lost his way.You are to present him with your finest creation."<br /><br />Fumbling with the items he was holding, Boldaim stared into the flaming figure which was staring to fade away.<br /><br />"But who will that man be? And who are you? What am i to present to him?" he managed to say in his surprise...<br /><br />"Well... " said the figure gently "i have many names... dwarves,elevs,gnomes,halflings have many names for me.But i am fond of the one humans use... Truthbringer"... <br /><br />The flames died down... <br />But the surprises didnt...<br />Boldaims vision went over to the piece of wood he was carving for so many hours... He picked it up...<br />There in his hand stood the figure of a knight clad in black battle armor, his breastplate decorated with black roses with long thorns.Around them a silken purple cord wieved a strange pattern...<br /><br />"By the thousent warhammers, ill be damned" he wispered at himself. Still looking at the wooden knight he reached with his other hand to remove the burned log and make space for another one.But what his hand closed on wasnt burned wood.It wasnt even warm by the fireplace.Wood has given its place into some strange black ore.<br />Noding his head in disbelief, he took the black ore and the wooden figure...<br />Cursing the weather he steped outside his house to a smaller building next to it...<br /><br />That night all the denizens of the Rathe mountains could swear that above the sounds of the frenzied wind and the storm, the sound of steel against steel echoed...<br /><br />----------<br /><br />My Honor is my Life...<br /><br />----------<br /><br />At the same time in a place not very far away from there... a portcullis was raised.<br /><br />"He must be crazy..." wispered a guard to the men that were pulling the weavy chains that lowered the brisge of the castle, as if he was afraid that the armored knight that was ridding the big black heavy warhorse could hear him over the raging winds...<br /><br />"I believe he is.." replied another one.. " Did you see his eyes through the visor of his Helm? I can swear that those are not the eyes of a sane man.."<br /><br />"But he just returned... " said a young squire... "Look at him and his horse... and that armor... that armor is so old, just like the one my grandfather used to describe to me , that the Great Lords in the Halls of Truth had the privilege to posses..."<br /><br />"He looks like he is hunting something... and he doesnt want that something to get away from him..." <br /><br />"Clear his way, let him pass.." said an old guard...<br />Noding a guantleted finger at the last who has spoken he said... "Even if he is hunting something... the last thing i would like now would be to stand between him and that something.."<br /><br />As soon as the lower end of the wooden bridge layed on the other end of the chasm, man and horse charged out side the Keep.<br />Like a demon that has awaken and wants to flex his muscles they rode outside... Just 200 yards away from the keep , they turned to face the castle. Horse raised in its behind legs in a mark of disapproval towards his master that ordered it to turn.<br />The knight raised the lance with the colors of Mithaniel Marr and the banner of the Keep.Waving it into the air thee times he drove the lance into the wet ground. Noding his head twice the warhorse acknowledged the cavaliers wish and returned towards the road...<br />Man and horse disaapeared into the darkness...<br /><br />As of some insane God was looking on Norrath that night, noone from the creatures that live and walk in the darkness dared to cross paths with the riding figure<br />Both living beings seemed locked with each other as they rode in the night...<br />...followin...<br />....<br />the smell of black roses...<br /><br />--------- <br /><br />Say willyou dream of me tonight... under moonless skies... <br /><br />---------<br /><br />The winds... The rain... his body in pain but he kept riding...<br />Voices wispered in his head...<br /><br />"We wonder the road sometimes...<br />Green forests,stars, and stories...<br />a secret time under three moons<br /><br />We walk the clouds sometimes<br />and ride on dragon fairies...<br />a drink with friends under three moons...<br /><br />Say will you dream with me tonight...<br /><br />And then we turn around <br />and find the forests gone<br />and find the stars and stories gone..<br />And then we turn around<br />and find the fairies gone..<br />and find the dragon fairies gone...<br /><br />Say will you dream with me tonight..."<br /><br />"... Yes my love... i will dream with you... wait for me... i am coming there..."<br />i<br />am<br />coming...<br /><br /><br />The heart has won...</span id="msg"></font></td>
                    </tr>
