                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2" color="#FFF8DC"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> The horses hoofs echoed in the stone path...<br />Sweat was running down the mailed neck of the warhorse, its breath was coming out with great difficulty each time.<br /><br />Its cavalier raised his head looking at the clouded sky...<br /><br />"I am deeply sorry friend, we will camp here tonight..." he wispered.<br />The horse noded its head in appreciation.<br />The man dismounted and removed the riding saddle of the horse. He lowered it gently to the wet ground and procedded in removing the horses barding...<br /><br />"We didnt have much luck today , did we friend?... I was hoping that someone in Shayye's Tavern would have seen her, but it seems that we must have been out of her tracks for a long time because she isnt exactly the type of person that would go unnoticed..."<br /><br />Allowing the horse to move to a place were it could graze, he removed his great helm and sighed...<br /><br />" Why do you mock me , Great One? Havent i served you well so far? Did i ask for anything in return? And there you are now, toying with your faithfull servant. Taking away from me what i love and hold dear most. "<br />He left his helm on the ground and prepared a small camp.<br />Taking off only those parts of his armor that would make him uncomfortable in sleeping, he stood for a bit glaring at the site of the Rathe mountains that layed in front of him...<br /><br />"So this is probably what stands between me and her...<br />Well there have been more difficult tasks in my life than this one...At least Great One keep her out of harms reach untill i find her..."<br /><br />Bowing his head deeply, he stood for a moment in silence...<br /><br />Deep into the unfriendly night... <br />Under the fiendish shade of Rathe mountains...<br />A bard so sung into the shadows....<br /><br />"I'm breaking but i cannot bear to<br />I'm staring but i cannot see you<br />For no more are you to lay by my side...<br />i'm straying in nightmares all the time...<br />Lorein, where have you gone?"<br /></span id="msg"></font></td>
