                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2" color="#FFF8DC"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Deudred covered himself as best as he could under his heavy winter cloack and moved on. Under normal circumstances , he would have been into his small house now, drinking his ale next to the warm fireplace.But the fur trade was the only thing that would keep his belly full and his skin warm and dry, and business has been very bad this winter.<br /><br />  Cursing the weather and the snow that has been falling for the last week covering the tracks of the brown bears he was hunting, he kept moving higher into the mountains.Suddenly as he took the next step, he found himself falling flat faced into the snow.<br /><br />"Tunare damn all the broken bowstrings, what the hell is it this time.." he muttered under his teeth as he tried to assemble himself and stand up. Embaraced he looked around, expecting to hear a mocking laughter from someone familiar, but he remembered that he was alone on this hunting expedition. Sighing loudly, he tried to find out what was the cause of his fall. There, half buried under the snow stood a big piece of shining metal. Unfortunatly, by the angle it was buried it was almost invisible inside the snow, one had to come sideways to see it.<br /><br />Droping to his knees, and leaving aside his longbow and quiver, he cleared the snow off the shining object. Examining it closely now, he realised that it was a bit familiar.<br /><br />"I'll be damned and turned to a frog, if this isnt horse plate barding..." he said loudly. A few glares around revieled him more metalic pieces. <br /><br />"What the hell is going on. One must be very stupid to cross these mountains with a horse in full barding. Or desperate enough"<br /><br />His late discovery woke up his curiousity. The bears wouldnt go anywhere. After all, so many years close to this territory, he considered his responsibility to partol the mountains and the lake close by, and be sure that everything was going on in natures way.<br />Raising up in haste, he grabed his bow and secured it behind his back.<br />Raising his gloved finger , he brought it to his forehead and closed his eyes. Feeling the magic flow within him, he wispered the same arcane words that have saved his life so many times as he brought to his mind the image of a wild and powerful wolf. Waving his hand into a strange pattern in the air, a mystical symbol appeared out of nowhere, it flashed once and dissapeared.Feeling the magic flowing within his body, he started to run. As his light leather boots touched the snow, one could swear he was more flying than running, leaving no prints on the fresh snow bed that has covered the Rathe mountains that winters morning....<br /><br />Edited by - Griffonheart Solamnus on 11/11/2002  09:10:21</span id="msg"></font></td>
