                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2" color="#FFF8DC"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Light was giving his place to darkness as the Night was weaving her beautyful cover over the lands of Norrath. As the creatures that take residence on the Rathe mounts and love and embrace the darkness were slowly opening their eyes, a howl broke the silence...<br />Then another, which was answered by yet another...<br />The wolves decided the time has come, hunger driving them mad.<br /><br />Noracor was cold and thirsty. Multiple wounds were covering his proud body, some of them even open. His blood was slowly spilling on the snow, and with it, his power too.The horse was a fierce opponent for the wolves. A dozen wolve bodies laying dead on the sheet of snow witnessed that fact.But the beasts have been patient. Slowly weakening the stalion, denying it sleep and rest, they were waiting for the time to strike. And all this time, the horse never left his masters side. Next to it, lay still the body of a plate armored figure, half covered in snow.Inside his gauntleted fist, could be seen a purple cord....<br /><br />The next howl was met by the wolves appearance. Slowly aproaching in a cresent formation, the beasts red eyes were focused on Noracor. The stalion raised its body in his behind legs in a defiant stance, and stood its ground...<br /><br />Rainstalker was literaly flying. His instict was urging him to move with haste, as he was discovering more left overs on the mountain later. Saddle bags, spare equipment... a riding saddle...<br />The tracks were showing him that the rider was on foot now, not wanting to push his faithfull animal more and cause its death.<br /><br />"I have to be getting close.Tunare guide me " .. he wispered. Then the first howl reached his ears.Cold sweat run down his spine. He knew this howl. Dire wolves closing on their cornered prey. Then he heard the second, and the third one...<br />Rushing forward like a mad demon, he removed his longbow from his back.He could see the scene clearly now.A horse backing slowly , keeping more than two dozen wolves at bay. But it was mortaly wounded, old scars on his legs reopened each time it was taking another step.Calmly but quickly he drove 6 arrows to the ground next to him as he knelt to one knee. <br />"Tunare guide my hand.", he prayed , as he let loose his first messanger of death. The arrow flew true, piercing the first wolves hide, passing though ribs and finally reaching its heart. The beast grinned and fell, motionless.In the blink of an eye, the second arrow struck, this time going through a wolves eye and crsuhing his scull on its way out.The rest of the beasts backed off a bit, but their hunger was too great to abandon such a feast. A third and fourth arrow met their victims, two more wove modies fell on the snow. Deudred threw back his head and let out an unearthy howl, a message to the predators that stood there, that this night they would have to seach for a new prey. The wolves backed up some more, then slowly turned and dissapeared in the cover of darkness, teeth bared nad grining.<br /><br />Leaving his bow aside, the ranger stood up slowly. <br />"This might prove challenging... " , he smiled to himself. He had heard about the trained warhorses loyalty to their master, and this particular warhorse was even more fierce than the best breed he had ever seen in his half elven life.He started to approach it, slowly, carefully, one hand extented infront of him as a sign of peace. Whispering soothing words, those that would even calm down the wildest animal, he reached the stalion.While it was backing away, it let the ranger touch his head and embrace it lovingly. Without stoping speaking to the animal, Deudred reached to a pouch that hanged from his belt and removed a mixture of green leaves,white dust and some strange liquid.Careful with one hand, he applied it to the animals open wounds.Stroking the stalions head steadily, his eyes searched the snow for any signs of its master. Then he saw the body laying close to him.Beside it was a big mark on the snow, a sign that the horse was laying close trying to keep its master warm.<br /><br />"Now lets see if he is still aliv-"... Hadnt been his superior reflexes he wouldnt have the time to avoid the deadly hoof. He rolled carefuly on the snow, and in a blink he was standing, his hand locked on the hilt of his longswod.The stalion was standing between him and the body, its eyes on him.<br /><br />Slowly he removed his hand , and smiled slightly...<br />"I understand you my friend.." he wispered, "but i will not harm your master..". He moved closer to it, "Allow me to tend to him as I did to you.."<br />Stroking the horses back , he knelt beside the body, fully knowing that the horse was still watching him carefully. He rolled the man over, and removed his great helm. On his moustache there were tiny bits of ice. Deudred removed his leather glove and reached to the mans neck, under his plate gorget.<br /><br />"Tunare be praised, by the thousand springs..." he said with surprise... "He is still alive..."<br /><br />Edited by - Griffonheart Solamnus on 11/11/2002  09:11:35</span id="msg"></font></td>
                    </tr>
