                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2" color="#FFF8DC"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Boldaim flexed his aged muschles as he felt the summer suns loving embrace warming him. Before him, stood a black warhorse and next to it, a figure clad in a beautiful black plate mail. The sun was stroking the carved breastplate, where one could recognize a thorny rose and a cord weaving a strange pattern around it.<br />  The armored figure dropped to his knee and bowed his head slightly in revere.<br /><br /> "Boldaim, I have no words to describe my feelings for you and what you did for me. If you are ever in a ..."<br /><br />  The ancient dwarf took two paces forward and brought his strong hand upon the mans shoulderguard.<br /><br /> "Nae mention it , lad. Whate't did, ae did in the name of Brell. Lads like ye are tough te find, like a flawless diamond in a mine of silver."<br /><br />  Stroking his beard with his other hand he continued..<br /><br /> "Then again it might be sometin ta do fer me , lad. Tell Delmair that I'll be waitin his worthless dwarven hide te come'ere and talk'bout things of old. Tell'm I got som'strong dwarven ale and all the time in the world."<br /> <br />  The old dwarf chuckled as he removed his hand...<br /><br /> "Now, be on yer way lad, ye have lots ta do. And remember... " he said in a deep voice as the armored figure mounted...<br /> "Seek and ye shall find lad.. Seek and ye shall find..."<br /><br />  The armored figure noded and gave the Knights salute to a friend, turned his mount towards the path and rode away into the morning suns light. The dwarf kept his vision locked on mand and horse until they both became tiny dots on the green bed of Rathe mounts. He brought to his mind the image of a half elven ranger carrying that young man in his arms and the wounded horse next to him that appeared one day into the middle of the heavy winter outside his small house. He has been expecting them, a burning figure had warned him before. Noe , the man fully recovered was riding outside, clad in dwarven made armor and carrying an ancient twohanded sword...<br /><br /><br /> "Karar bea Brell... " he wispered slowly as he wiped a small tear with the back of his hand... "Friends meet at Brell.."<br /> <br />  He turned around and entered his small warm house..<br /></span id="msg"></font></td>
