                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2" color="#FFF8DC"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> As slight waves of air breezed through the visor of his plate helm and stroked his clean shaven chin, the armored figgure patted lovingly the barding of his warhorshe at its neck.<br /><br />"I know the feeling , old friend. I understand how restless you have been during the past weeks, I could sence it in your behaviour. Along with you, I too wished to ride outside in the morning sun..."<br /><br />Leaning ahead, he closed his eyes slightly, leaving himself to the moment. An image flashed in his head, a beautiful young face, blue eyes covered in sorrow, blonde hair running down freely...<br />His heart stirred suddenly.<br />He was not yet done..<br />He remembered...<br /><br />"The Ro Desert.." he snapped, " In its Southern part there should be a camp. We will start our search from there again. But before that, its the swamps we need to ... "<br /><br />Opening his eyes, he ralized that Noracor was already running at almost top speed towards the Innothule Swamps.<br />He smiled crookingly...<br /><br />And as the morning breeze kept whistling through the slits of his helm, he swore he could recognize the rythme of an old song his mother used to sing to him so long ago..<br /><br /> "Trees have dropped their leaves<br />  Clouds their waters<br />  All this burden is killing me<br />  Distance is covering your way<br />  Tears your memory<br />  All this beauty is killing me<br />  Oh, do you care, I still feel for you<br />  So aware, what should be lost is there<br />  I fear I will never find anyone<br />  I know my greatest pain is yet to come<br />  Will we find each other in the dark<br />  My... long lost love "<br /><br /><br />...<br /><br />He was not yet done.</span id="msg"></font></td>
