                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2" color="#FFF8DC"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> .... He could see the back of the man. He seemed to be dressed in some kind of military uniform and he was walking in a slow and steady pace. He was holding something in his arms, it was more of a someone though...<br />A hand was across his shoulders and a pair of finely curved legs could be seen , extending at the side of his right arm.He watched carefully as the figure aproached slowly a large bed and layed the body upon the white sheets. It was a young girl in her low twenties, her face almost covered from a waterfall of blonde hair. She wasnt moving at all.<br /><br />He walked slowly towards the bed, a bad taste reached his mouth and he stirred slightly as if an imaginary hand squized his stomach.<br /><br />Now the man was sitting on the bed next to the girl, which was covered in a blue silken robe, decorated with familiar symbols. Mythaniel Marrs. The twist in his stomach was getting hander and harder as he came closer and stopped next to the bed. <br />Something was telling him to pull away from there, to stop looking , but it seemed as if his legs had a will of their own and kept him pinned there. <br />The mans right hand reached to her chin and stroked it slightly revealing her face, a familair face from the past, one not to be seen many a moons ago.<br />He felt his heart stop beating as an unearthly howl came upon his lungs... <br /><br /> "NOOOoooooo............"<br /><br />He woke up, covered in sweat, both of his hands locked upon the sides of the small wooden bed, the blood veins on his neck were swollen, as if ready to explode. The howl was still echoing in his ears as he shook his head violently trying to chase away the image that had caused this.<br />Covering his head with his hands, he tried to bring himself into control..<br />Slowly, he stood up and walked towards a small bucket of water. Taking two handfulls he threw it in his face. The cold water felt good, waking him up fully within seconds. A small glance outside revealed that the night was just starting to fall. Giving a silent prayer that noone had awaken to investigate the cause of the howl, he started to don his armor. <br />The night was till young, and there was pleanty of time to reach the Oasis of Marr, before the temperature had dropped low enough to make traveling impossible.The thought of the sea he so loved to visit along with his father when he was a younger boy , made him focus and work faster.Like an old veteran full of battle scars who was used to work without a canddles light, he was done within minutes. Reaching to his belt pouch he removed two platinum pieces and left them on the pillow along with a prayer for the denizens of the camp who were kind enough to allow him rest in one of their tents. <br />Walking outside, he found Noracor standing next to the tent, nodding his head slightly as his right front hoove was digging into the sand.<br /><br />Smiling to himself, he reached for the reigns of his faithful mount and he strapped on the saddle. <br /><br />"Thank you for watching over me yet another night my friend. Most kind of you "  he wispered to the horse as he started walking beside it, reigns in his right hand, helm in the other.<br /><br />Moving silently between the tents, he noticed two pair of eyes staring at him. Turning to face em, he found a small boy standing next to a tent holding a wooden toy sword almost as big as him. Next to it was a beautiful young girl with a handfull of night lilys in her embrace.Both of em were not older than a decade...<br /><br />As he passed close to them he felt their eyes penetrating him as a wave of security, warmth and power overwelmed him. He stood there for a moment, looking back at the two kinds, then silently turning ahead resuming his course...<br /><br />When he was well away of them, the girl turned to face the boy with an angry look in her eyes. <br /><br />"Dear brother what have you done to this man? I sence great sorrow within him."<br /><br />The boy was still staring at the knights figure as he spoke slowly...<br /><br />"I have done nothing to him , my dear sister.His destiny is his own, you know. I just gave it a gentle push..."<br /><br />"A gentle push?!? " The girl was now hodling her flowers in one hand and was nodding her other to the boy.She was unearthly beautiful and calm...<br /><br />"His loyalties stand with you until his last breath. Yet you insist on breaking him. Why? "<br /><br />"He needs to be broken , sister. For what awaits him ahead, needs him strong , not only in body but in soul too. And speaking of that, what interest is of yours in him? I thought you were too buzy playing with that wood elf who was trying to enter our barbarian culture to take notice on anything else."<br /><br />The girl gave a toyful stroke with her flowers at the boys chest.<br /><br />"It matters me, you know. Because what you do, involves someone else, who is out in your name too."<br /><br />The boy turned and smiled warmly towards her, his eyes the eyes of a ten year old were filled with the wisdom of ages. <br /><br />"He will be a valuable piece in the chessboard, sister. Now that he will be broken, he will be the perfect tool for the plans."<br /><br />He started walking slowly..<br /><br />The girl starred at him for a while, then a broad smile crossed her face.<br /><br />"So you think, brother. But there is something that you dont count , in your masterfull plans. Love will find a way.. Love always finds a way.."<br /><br />Kissing the lilys, she scattered them to the winds and started walking behind him..<br /><br />As the lilys pedals were drifting in the nights breeze, a soft song broke the nights silence..<br /><br />  No Love,<br />  No Truth,<br />  No nothing, <br />  You dont exist<br />  Not anymore<br />  The sun rises again ending the world where it began.<br />  Is there anything left?<br /><br />...<br /><br /><br />He was not yet done.</span id="msg"></font></td>
                    </tr>
